eat was just rice and salt.

00:09:04.860 --> 00:09:06.280
Now, you heard that correct.

00:09:06.280 --> 00:09:10.600
It's rice and salt. If
he had a chili in a week,

00:09:10.600 --> 00:09:12.600
he considered himself
extremely lucky.

00:09:12.600 --> 00:09:14.440
That's how bad he was.

00:09:14.440 --> 00:09:17.950
And because of the
excess of rice and salt,

00:09:17.950 --> 00:09:20.539
he developed diabetes
as well as hypertension.

00:09:20.539 --> 00:09:23.080
And these are two diseases you
cannot treat by giving medical

00:09:23.080 --> 00:09:25.290
care once every six
months or a year.

00:09:25.290 --> 00:09:28.300
He needs to have continuous
monitoring and follow-up.

00:09:28.300 --> 00:09:31.020
So that's why we developed
this weekly model,

00:09:31.020 --> 00:09:33.770
and with inspiration from
great leaders in India who

00:09:33.770 --> 00:09:35.690
have really struggled
for our freedom

00:09:35.690 --> 00:09:37.860
and emphasized the need
for selfless service

00:09:37.860 --> 00:09:40.190
to the society, we
started these activities

00:09:40.190 --> 00:09:42.660
on a very noble day,
which is our father

00:09:42.660 --> 00:09:45.490
of the nation, Mahatma
Gandhiji's birthday on 2

00:09:45.490 --> 00:09:47.230
October, 2006.

00:09:47.230 --> 00:09:51.650
And I'm proud to stand here and
say that for the last 10 years,

00:09:51.650 --> 00:09:54.360
not a single day has been
missed in terms of these service

00:09:54.360 --> 00:09:55.190
activities.

00:09:55.190 --> 00:09:58.030
Every week, rain or
shine, our volunteers

00:09:58.030 --> 00:09:59.990
have gone to these
remote villages.

00:09:59.990 --> 00:10:02.700
It started off with one
village, in Uttar Pradesh,

00:10:02.700 --> 00:10:06.360
and today it's expanded
to more than 250 villages.

00:10:06.360 --> 00:10:08.290
Every week we have
been providing

00:10:08.290 --> 00:10:11.190
free health care and free food.

00:10:11.190 --> 00:10:14.330
Now, you wouldn't believe--
you may think, what is this one

00:10:14.330 --> 00:10:15.950
meal a week going to do?

00:10:15.950 --> 00:10:18.320
But that one meal
a week is going

00:10:18.320 --> 00:10:21.690
to really substitute for their
nutrition and other aspects

00:10:21.690 --> 00:10:22.800
that they require.

00:10:22.800 --> 00:10:25.740
And that creates a lot of
goodwill in these villages,

00:10:25.740 --> 00:10:27.899
that somebody is coming
in, providing us free food.

00:10:27.899 --> 00:10:30.440
And then that's the best way to
invite them for participating

00:10:30.440 --> 00:10:32.250
in these medical care programs.

00:10:32.250 --> 00:10:34.120
And a lot of times
we find diabetes,

00:10:34.120 --> 00:10:35.830
hypertension is the
number one, number

00:10:35.830 --> 00:10:37.400
two problems in our country.

00:10:37.400 --> 00:10:40.552
And a lot of times we also
find body pains and so on.

00:10:40.552 --> 00:10:42.010
And when we
investigate further, we

00:10:42.010 --> 00:10:43.530
find that the water
is contaminated

00:10:43.530 --> 00:10:44.970
with flouride content.

00:10:44.970 --> 00:10:47.990
Because of that, they have a
lot of problems, and so on.

00:10:47.990 --> 00:10:52.670
And some of these villages are
so remote that these villagers

00:10:52.670 --> 00:10:55.220
don't even know that there
is a hospital existing,

00:10:55.220 --> 00:10:56.390
even 10 kilometers away.

00:10:56.390 --> 00:10:59.530
They can't afford it, because
if they miss that day's work,

00:10:59.530 --> 00:11:01.560
they lose their seven
rupees, and they won't

00:11:01.560 --> 00:11:04.050
have food for the next day.

00:11:04.050 --> 00:11:05.240
So it's really bad.

00:11:05.240 --> 00:11:07.020
And for some of
these villages, we

00:11:07.020 --> 00:11:09.900
had to develop a different
approach, using technology,

00:11:09.900 --> 00:11:11.650
to go reach them out.

00:11:11.650 --> 00:11:14.120
And what we do here is
we actually maintain

00:11:14.120 --> 00:11:15.966
patient booklets for
each and every villager

00:11:15.966 --> 00:11:18.090
so that when they come the
next week, even if there

00:11:18.090 --> 00:11:19.964
is a different doctor,
he knows what medicine

00:11:19.964 --> 00:11:21.131
was given the previous week.

00:11:21.131 --> 00:11:22.464
So there is a continuous follow.

00:11:22.464 --> 00:11:24.220
And we actually
computerized all the data.

00:11:24.220 --> 00:11:26.780
It's available on the cloud,
and a doctor sitting in the US

00:11:26.780 --> 00:11:29.480
can actually monitor what's
happening to that patient.

00:11:29.480 --> 00:11:30.840
But that was just not enough.

00:11:30.840 --> 00:11:32.610
We had to go develop
better technologies

00:11:32.610 --> 00:11:34.860
to go reach out to
these remote villages.

00:11:34.860 --> 00:11:37.890
So last year we
launched a technology

00:11:37.890 --> 00:11:40.550
which is really the world's
first mobile delivery

00:11:40.550 --> 00:11:43.650
solution, which is a
bus called SAIWHEELS.

00:11:43.650 --> 00:11:46.810
It stands for Society
Advancement and Improvement

00:11:46.810 --> 00:11:50.680
by Water, Health Care,
Education, Energy, Through Love

00:11:50.680 --> 00:11:51.750
and Service.

00:11:51.750 --> 00:11:54.920
And this bus was the
world's first integrated bus

00:11:54.920 --> 00:11:57.650
which had solar panels
on top of it, which

00:11:57.650 --> 00:11:58.926
can generate electricity.

00:11:58.926 --> 00:12:00.800
There is mobile clinic
and then there is also

00:12:00.800 --> 00:12:03.280
a mobile classroom with
a library and so on.

00:12:03.280 --> 00:12:05.100
And then there is
also a water purifier.

00:12:05.100 --> 00:12:07.460
Now, you can see in this
image, some of these kids

00:12:07.460 --> 00:12:10.740
have never, ever stepped
into a school in their life.

00:12:10.740 --> 00:12:14.170
This is the first time they
get experience to learning

00:12:14.170 --> 00:12:18.120
something with state-of-the-art
multimedia equipments

00:12:18.120 --> 00:12:19.620
and things like that on the bus.

00:12:19.620 --> 00:12:22.520
So that really triggers
the interest in them.

00:12:22.520 --> 00:12:24.320
We go there only once a week.

00:12:24.320 --> 00:12:26.820
It's not enough to give them
just once a week education.

00:12:26.820 --> 00:12:28.660
But it triggers
interest in them.

00:12:28.660 --> 00:12:31.640
That's what drives them to go
to school, or do better in life.

00:12:31.640 --> 00:12:34.500
Otherwise these kids wander
around doing nothing.

00:12:34.500 --> 00:12:37.789
And they're struggling for food,
struggling for basic water,

00:12:37.789 --> 00:12:38.580
and other problems.

00:12:38.580 --> 00:12:42.640
We actually went to a village
near Raipur in Chhattisgarh,

00:12:42.640 --> 00:12:44.220
and this village
is called Persada.

00:12:44.220 --> 00:12:46.530
We were shocked because
we went to this place

00:12:46.530 --> 00:12:48.030
where there's a lake.

00:12:48.030 --> 00:12:49.450
The buffaloes are bathing there.

00:12:49.450 --> 00:12:51.565
People are washing their
clothes over there.

00:12:51.565 --> 00:12:52.190
And guess what?

00:12:52.190 --> 00:12:55.119
The children came and started
drinking that same water.

00:12:55.119 --> 00:12:56.410
Now, we live in Silicon Valley.

00:12:56.410 --> 00:12:58.450
How can we accept this?

00:12:58.450 --> 00:13:01.390
So that's where-- this bus
actually has a water purifier,

00:13:01.390 --> 00:13:03.210
so when it goes to the
village, it actually

00:13:03.210 --> 00:13:05.750
delivers pure drinking
water to the villages.

00:13:05.750 --> 00:13:08.560
And we encourage the villagers
to fill up a 20-liter can

00:13:08.560 --> 00:13:10.566
so that is good enough
at least for a week.

00:13:10.566 --> 00:13:11.940
If you give them
pure water, that

00:13:11.940 --> 00:13:15.320
cuts down half of the
health care problems.

00:13:15.320 --> 00:13:17.800
So we are also collaborating
with Stanford University.

00:13:17.800 --> 00:13:20.500
We actually hosted a conference
called Science for Society,

00:13:20.500 --> 00:13:23.220
using which we are coming up
with an ideal village program,

00:13:23.220 --> 00:13:25.450
where using energy, it's
going to self-sustain

00:13:25.450 --> 00:13:27.571
all these activities
moving forward.

00:13:27.571 --> 00:13:28.820
But that alone was not enough.

00:13:28.820 --> 00:13:32.250
We found a lot of children
having heart diseases.

00:13:32.250 --> 00:13:34.110
And I'll give you an example.

00:13:34.110 --> 00:13:38.280
This one little baby, her
name is [? Twinkle Sahu. ?]

00:13:38.280 --> 00:13:41.030
And she actually
had a heart problem.

00:13:41.030 --> 00:13:43.000
Her parents knew
about it, and they

00:13:43.000 --> 00:13:44.910
knew that she was almost dying.

00:13:44.910 --> 00:13:47.090
Literally, her
days were counted.

00:13:47.090 --> 00:13:51.310
But these parents were making
less than $100 a month,

00:13:51.310 --> 00:13:55.200
and a heart surgery in India
cost much more than $5,000,

00:13:55.200 --> 00:13:56.350
$10,000.

00:13:56.350 --> 00:13:57.880
And they just
couldn't afford it.

00:13:57.880 --> 00:13:59.440
I mean, in our
country here, even

00:13:59.440 --> 00:14:01.610
if our pet is
affected by a problem,

00:14:01.610 --> 00:14:03.590
we all worry about it so much.

00:14:03.590 --> 00:14:06.460
But here they know that
the child is going to die.

00:14:06.460 --> 00:14:07.770
What can they do?

00:14:07.770 --> 00:14:10.200
And that's where we
started supporting

00:14:10.200 --> 00:14:13.120
a completely free hospital.

00:14:13.120 --> 00:14:14.710
It was built in the
shape of a heart

00:14:14.710 --> 00:14:17.300
in a place called Raipur,
Chhattisgarh, which

00:14:17.300 --> 00:14:18.574
is really the heart of India.

00:14:18.574 --> 00:14:20.490
If you look at the India
map, that's literally

00:14:20.490 --> 00:14:22.420
where exactly the heart is.

00:14:22.420 --> 00:14:26.100
And this hospital was
inaugurated in 2012

00:14:26.100 --> 00:14:28.400
in November, and it
has been providing

00:14:28.400 --> 00:14:32.610
heart surgeries completely free
of cost for these children.

00:14:32.610 --> 00:14:35.320
And since their
inception, this hospital

00:14:35.320 --> 00:14:37.310
has benefited so many people.

00:14:37.310 --> 00:14:39.880
And early this year, our
prime minister Modiji

00:14:39.880 --> 00:14:41.690
came and visited this hospital.

00:14:41.690 --> 00:14:44.730
This is really evolving into
one of the state-of-the-art

00:14:44.730 --> 00:14:47.640
hospitals serving all the
communities from all over

00:14:47.640 --> 00:14:48.580
India.

